Keys to growing your instagram🔑

👨‍👩‍👦‍👦Value- Be sure to provide value for your targeted audience. Everyone wants to learn something. If you can solve a problem that your audience might have or that you used to have you will get the followers your looking for. Think of this way, would you follow your page and why? 

🗣️ Be Unique and Aunthentic- everyone wants to be someone on social media in 2023 and now its harder to stand out. I dont believe any of us are self made we all have copied someone or learned from others who paved the way before us. Use your favorite influencers content for ideas but never duplicate their videos you must make them your own. Every piece of content you create must be a reflection of you. Its ok to get ideas from others but make sure you make it “YOU”

🎙️Engage with your followers- im a firm beleiver that you must give support to get it. People often times post and wonder why no one comments or shares their videos. You must set the tone and engage first! Connecting with others also builds RELATIONSHIPS & TRUST which will go a long way in any industry. 

🎬 POST CONSISTENTLY- this is a no brainer, not just for social media but for any industry and in life. Does that mean you have to post every day ? No! But you get what you put out. 
Create a schedule/goal of how many times a week you can commit to then accomplish it for a period of time then challenge youe self to double that amount until youve reached your desired goal. Any one can say they dont have time to post but we all have the same amount of time in a day. Its more of HOW BADLY DO YOU WANT IT? 

❌ CREATING THE PERFECT VIDEO
Perfection is nonexistent. Theres no perfect video, perfect time to post, or perfect time to start, The best time is now. The more you post the better you get. So what are you waiting for ?

The HOOK is the most critical part of posting a video l. You have very little time to capture your audience’s attention. So when you create your videos GET TO THE POINT! People’s attention spans  are zero. #contentcreation #contentips #socialmedia #contentcreator

Gaining clientele thru social media can really help you scale your business and attract a higher paying clientele. But here’s 3 things I wish I knew when I first started promoting myself on social media that hopefully help you🙏🙏

1.”Only posting the finished result of your service”
Everyone in your industry is posting their work what makes you stand out over the competition? Yes you might be good at what you do but it tends to get saturated thru the feed with everyone else posting the same thing as you. Show your audience why they should book with you and separates you from everyone else and “SHOW YOU IN THE VIDEO”

2.”Not educating your clients and your Audience”
People want to learn! When you can educate your Audience and teach them something they didn’t know about their hair or the service you provide.

3. “Never tagging your clients when you post them and not showing testimonials”
Always be sure to tag your clients so they can repost or share your video which in turn can get you a leads from their friends and followers. Lastly be sure to post testimonials to show the quality service you provide to your clients. 

#barber #babrertips #customerservice #fullservicebarber

When I started my barber career I was really not a fan of low tapers in the back for many reasons. 

1. I felt like their wasn’t a lot of contrast in the hair cut.
2. I hated nothing more then seeing a V neck and seeing a 2 finger width push back on the neck line 
3. And most of all as the consumer hated that my taper would grow back in 2 days because there wasn’t a lot of contrast on my cut.
